globs: packages/remotion/**/*.tsx, apps/worker/worker/jobs/render.py, apps/worker/worker/media/**/*.py
alwaysApply: false
---

Use these rules for clip generation, Remotion captions, vertical formatting, and thumbnails.

Clip rendering:
- Render clips from approved highlight candidates or user-selected start/end times.
- Use FFmpeg to cut source.mp4 into clip.mp4.
- Store clips under data/videos/{project_id}/clips/.
- Store clip metadata in the clips table.
- Verify rendered files exist before updating the database as complete.

Clip timing:
- Store start/end timestamps in milliseconds.
- Keep clip duration within user-requested size when practical.
- Supported target lengths may include 30 seconds, 60 seconds, and custom ranges.
- When snapping to scene boundaries, preserve the clip's narrative context.

Aspect ratios:
- Support original aspect ratio.
- Support 9:16 vertical short-form format.
- Later support 1:1 if needed.
- Do not crop important visual content carelessly.

Captions:
- Use transcript word timestamps to render captions.
- Captions should be editable before final render when possible.
- Remotion should handle caption overlays.
- Caption styles should be parameterized, not hardcoded.
- Support personalized caption styles over time.
- Keep caption text readable on mobile.

Remotion:
- Keep Remotion components in packages/remotion.
- Keep reusable caption rendering in Captions.tsx or focused subcomponents.
- Avoid mixing database access into Remotion components.
- Pass rendering data into Remotion through props or input files.

Thumbnails:
- Extract candidate frames from the clip or source video.
- Compose thumbnails using Satori or another deterministic rendering method.
- Store thumbnails under data/videos/{project_id}/thumbnails/.
- Store thumbnail paths in the database.
- Do not overwrite previous thumbnail variants unless explicitly intended.

Do not:
- Bake captions into the only copy of a clip if an uncaptioned version is still needed.
- Hardcode caption style values throughout the codebase.
- Generate thumbnails that misrepresent the clip content.
